     1	# waveplan-ps
     2	
     3	`waveplan-ps` is a local observer for waveplan execution. It loads
     4	explicitly-specified execution-wave plans, waveplan state sidecars, SWIM
     5	journals, txtstore notes, and SWIM step logs, then renders a live terminal
     6	view or a deterministic one-shot text snapshot.
     7	
     8	## Build
     9	
    10	```bash
    11	go build -o waveplan-ps ./cmd/waveplan-ps
    12	```
    13	
    14	## Usage
    15	
    16	Render one text snapshot and exit:
    17	
    18	```bash
    19	./waveplan-ps \
    20	  --once \
    21	  --plan ../docs/plans/2026-05-12-waveplan-ps-execution-waves.json \
    22	  --state ../docs/plans/2026-05-12-waveplan-ps-execution-waves.json.state.json \
    23	  --journal ../docs/plans/2026-05-12-waveplan-ps-execution-schedule.json.journal.json \
    24	  --log-dir ../docs/plans/.waveplan
    25	```
    26	
    27	Run the live terminal observer:
    28	
    29	```bash
    30	./waveplan-ps \
    31	  --config docs/waveplan-ps-config-example.yaml \
    32	  --interval 2s
    33	```
    34	
    35	You can also supply the same explicit paths through environment variables:
    36	
    37	```bash
    38	export WAVEPLAN_PLAN=/abs/path/to/plan-execution-waves.json
    39	export WAVEPLAN_STATE=/abs/path/to/plan-execution-state.json
    40	export WAVEPLAN_JOURNAL=/abs/path/to/plan-execution-journal.json
    41	./waveplan-ps --config docs/waveplan-ps-config-example.yaml --interval 2s
    42	```
    43	
    44	## Flags
    45	
    46	| flag | default | description |
    47	|---|---:|---|
    48	| `--config` | empty | YAML config file. Explicit CLI paths are appended to config path lists. |
    49	| `--once` | `false` | Render one text snapshot and exit. Without this flag, the live TUI runs until interrupted. |
    50	| `--plan` | empty | Execution-waves plan path. Repeatable. Falls back to `WAVEPLAN_PLAN` when omitted. |
    51	| `--state` | empty | Waveplan state sidecar path. Repeatable. Falls back to `WAVEPLAN_STATE` when omitted. |
    52	| `--journal` | empty | SWIM journal sidecar path. Repeatable. Falls back to `WAVEPLAN_JOURNAL` when omitted. |
    53	| `--note` | empty | Markdown txtstore note path. Repeatable. |
    54	| `--log-dir` | empty | Directory root to recursively scan for SWIM log files. Repeatable. This is not a glob pattern. |
    55	| `--interval` | `1s` | Live refresh interval, parsed as a Go duration such as `500ms`, `2s`, or `1m`. |
    56	| `--tail-limit` | `10` | Maximum waveplan tail rows to render. Values less than or equal to zero render all rows. |
    57	| `--journal-limit` | `10` | Maximum SWIM journal events to render. Values less than or equal to zero render all events. |
    58	| `--expand-first-wave` | `true` | Initial display setting for the first wave. Passing the flag overrides config. |
    59	
    60	## Config
    61	
    62	Plan/state/journal/note lists are explicit file paths. Only `log_dirs` remains
    63	directory-based because SWIM log discovery is fan-out over many step log files.
    64	
    65	```yaml
    66	log_dirs:
    67	  - ../docs/plans/.waveplan
    68	display:
    69	  expand_first_wave: true
    70	```
    71	
    72	`display.expand_first_wave` defaults to `true` when omitted. Set it to `false`
    73	in YAML when the first wave should start collapsed.
    74	
    75	## Explicit Inputs
    76	
    77	`waveplan-ps` no longer scans directories for plans, state files, journals, or
    78	notes. Those are loaded only from explicit CLI flags, config path lists, or the
    79	`WAVEPLAN_PLAN`, `WAVEPLAN_STATE`, and `WAVEPLAN_JOURNAL` environment
    80	variables.
    81	
    82	SWIM logs are still discovered under configured `log_dirs`. Valid SWIM log
    83	filenames are:
    84	
    85	Valid SWIM log actions are `implement`, `review`, `review_r<N>`, `fix`,
    86	`fix_r<N>`, `end_review`, and `finish`. Log files are correlated to units by
    87	the task-id segment embedded in `step_id`, so `T1.1` does not match `T11.1`.
    88	
    89	Malformed log filenames under `log_dirs` fail the snapshot or live poll with a
    90	parse error. Put unrelated logs outside configured log roots.

