   252	  --out "$SCHEDULE" \
   253	  --bootstrap-state
   254	```
   255	
   256	If you do not want to use the installed default agents file, pass one directly:
   257	
   258	```bash
   259	waveplan-cli swim compile-schedule \
   260	  --plan "$PLAN" \
   261	  --agents tests/swim/fixtures/waveagents.json \
   262	  --out "$SCHEDULE" \
   263	  --bootstrap-state
   264	```
   265	
   266	Inspect the next step without mutation:
   267	
   268	```bash
   269	waveplan-cli swim next --schedule "$SCHEDULE"
   270	```
   271	
   272	Apply one step:
   273	
   274	```bash
   275	waveplan-cli swim step --apply --schedule "$SCHEDULE"
   276	```
   277	
   278	Apply until a boundary:
   279	
   280	```bash
   281	waveplan-cli swim run --schedule "$SCHEDULE" --until review
   282	waveplan-cli swim run --schedule "$SCHEDULE" --until fix
   283	waveplan-cli swim run --schedule "$SCHEDULE" --until seq:4
   284	waveplan-cli swim run --schedule "$SCHEDULE" --until step:S1_T1.1_finish
   285	```
   286	
   287	Inspect recent journal events:
   288	
   289	```bash
   290	waveplan-cli swim journal --schedule "$SCHEDULE" --tail 5
   291	```
   292	
   293	Validate artifacts:
   294	
   295	```bash
   296	waveplan-cli swim validate --kind schedule --in "$SCHEDULE"
   297	waveplan-cli swim validate --kind journal --in "${SCHEDULE%.json}.journal.json"
   298	```
   299	
   300	### SWIM Terminology
   301	
   302	| Term | Meaning |
   303	|------|---------|
   304	| `schedule` | v2 JSON list of execution rows. Each row has `seq`, `step_id`, `task_id`, `action`, `requires`, `produces`, and `invoke.argv`. |
   305	| `journal` | append-only v1 JSON event log. The `cursor` points at the next schedule row to execute. |
   306	| `state` | waveplan `<plan>.state.json`; task status is derived as `available`, `taken`, `review_taken`, `review_ended`, or `completed`. |
   307	| `dispatch action` | an action that hands work to an external agent CLI and must produce a dispatch receipt: `implement`, `review`, `fix`. |
   308	| `dispatch receipt` | durable proof that the target CLI accepted the prompt, written under `.waveplan/swim/<schedule-basename>/receipts/`. |
   309	| `incomplete_dispatch` | state advanced but receipt is missing; rerun the same SWIM step to redeliver the prompt. |
   310	| `fix` | dispatch action that transitions `review_taken -> taken` and sends prior review stdout to the implementer. |
   311	| `fix round` | preplanned `fix -> review` pair. Step IDs may use `_rN`, e.g. `S3_T1.1_fix_r1`. |
   312	
   313	### Step Lifecycle
   314	
   315	The standard emitted lifecycle is:
   316	
   317	```text
   318	implement   available    -> taken
   319	review      taken        -> review_taken
   320	end_review  review_taken -> review_ended
   321	finish      review_ended -> completed
   322	```
   323	
   324	The runtime also supports preplanned fix cycles:
   325	
   326	```text
   327	implement   available    -> taken
   328	review      taken        -> review_taken
   329	fix         review_taken -> taken
   330	review_r2   taken        -> review_taken
   331	end_review  review_taken -> review_ended
   332	finish      review_ended -> completed
   333	```
   334	
   335	Current `wp-emit-wave-execution.sh` emits the standard lifecycle. If a schedule
   336	contains `fix` rows, SWIM validates and executes them, and `wp-task-to-agent.sh
   337	--mode fix` attaches the prior review stdout via `SWIM_PRIOR_STDOUT_PATH`.
   338	That launcher path depends on a configured waveplan CLI/MCP that supports
   339	`start_fix <task_id>`.
   340	
   341	### Dispatch Safety
   342	
   343	For `implement`, `review`, and `fix`, SWIM injects these env vars into the
   344	invoked launcher:
   345	
   346	```text
   347	SWIM_DISPATCH_RECEIPT_PATH
   348	SWIM_STEP_ID
   349	SWIM_TASK_ID
   350	SWIM_ACTION
   351	SWIM_PRIOR_STDOUT_PATH   # fix only, when a prior review stdout log exists
   352	```
   353	
   354	The step is `applied` only when both conditions hold:
   355	
   356	```text
   357	runtime state == row.produces.task_status
   358	dispatch receipt exists
   359	```
   360	
   361	If state moved but the receipt is missing, SWIM returns `incomplete_dispatch`.
   362	Do not manually advance the journal; rerun:
   363	
   364	```bash
   365	waveplan-cli swim step --apply --schedule "$SCHEDULE"
   366	```
   367	
   368	### Boundaries and Inquiries
   369	
   370	SWIM observes execution and stops at expected boundaries. It does not approve

