     2	
     3	`waveplan-ps` is a local observer for waveplan execution. It loads
     4	explicitly-specified execution-wave plans, waveplan state sidecars, SWIM
     5	journals, SWIM review-schedule sidecars, txtstore notes, and SWIM step logs,
     6	then renders a live terminal view or a deterministic one-shot text snapshot.
     7	
     8	## Build
     9	
    10	```bash
    11	go build -o waveplan-ps ./cmd/waveplan-ps
    12	```
    13	
