    47	
    48	| flag | default | description |
    49	|---|---:|---|
    50	| `--config` | empty | YAML config file. Explicit CLI paths are appended to config path lists. |
    51	| `--once` | `false` | Render one text snapshot and exit. Without this flag, the live TUI runs until interrupted. |
    52	| `--plan` | empty | Execution-waves plan path. Repeatable. Falls back to `WAVEPLAN_PLAN` when omitted. |
    53	| `--state` | empty | Waveplan state sidecar path. Repeatable. Falls back to `WAVEPLAN_STATE` when omitted. |
    54	| `--journal` | empty | SWIM journal sidecar path. Repeatable. Falls back to `WAVEPLAN_JOURNAL` when omitted. |
    55	| `--review-schedule` | empty | SWIM review schedule sidecar path. Repeatable. Falls back to `WAVEPLAN_SCHED_REVIEW` when omitted. |
    56	| `--note` | empty | Markdown txtstore note path. Repeatable. |
    57	| `--log-dir` | empty | Directory root to recursively scan for SWIM log files. Repeatable. This is not a glob pattern. |
    58	| `--interval` | `1s` | Live refresh interval, parsed as a Go duration such as `500ms`, `2s`, or `1m`. |
    59	| `--tail-limit` | `10` | Maximum waveplan tail rows to render. Values less than or equal to zero render all rows. |
    60	| `--journal-limit` | `10` | Maximum SWIM journal events to render. Values less than or equal to zero render all events. |
    61	| `--expand-first-wave` | `true` | Initial display setting for the first wave. Passing the flag overrides config. |
    62	
    63	## Config
    64	
    65	Plan/state/journal/review-schedule/note lists are explicit file paths. Only
    66	`log_dirs` remains directory-based because SWIM log discovery is fan-out over
    67	many step log files.
    68	
    69	```yaml
    70	review_schedule_paths:
    71	  - ../docs/plans/2026-05-14-swim-review-schedule-sidecar-execution-review-schedule.json
    72	log_dirs:
    73	  - ../docs/plans/.waveplan
    74	display:
    75	  expand_first_wave: true
    76	```
    77	
    78	`display.expand_first_wave` defaults to `true` when omitted. Set it to `false`
    79	in YAML when the first wave should start collapsed.
    80	
    81	## Explicit Inputs
    82	
    83	`waveplan-ps` no longer scans directories for plans, state files, journals,
    84	review schedules, or notes. Those are loaded only from explicit CLI flags,
    85	config path lists, or the `WAVEPLAN_PLAN`, `WAVEPLAN_STATE`,
    86	`WAVEPLAN_JOURNAL`, and `WAVEPLAN_SCHED_REVIEW` environment variables.
    87	
    88	SWIM logs are still discovered under configured `log_dirs`. Valid SWIM log
    89	filenames are:
    90	
    91	Valid SWIM log actions are `implement`, `review`, `review_r<N>`, `fix`,
    92	`fix_r<N>`, `end_review`, and `finish`. Log files are correlated to units by
    93	the task-id segment embedded in `step_id`, so `T1.1` does not match `T11.1`.
    94	
    95	Malformed log filenames under `log_dirs` fail the snapshot or live poll with a
    96	parse error. Put unrelated logs outside configured log roots.

